                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Muḥtasham, ʻAlī ibn Aḥmad, 1499 or 1500-1587 or 1588</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">محتشم، علي بن احمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en">A tarkib-band in praise of 'Ali.</title>
                     <note>Possibly written by Muhtasham Kashi. On back cover: armorial bookplate of N.B. Edmonstone. Held in a British tooled red morocco case with flaps and tapes. The poet calls himself Kashi and says he is at Amul. Possibly the fifteenth-century poet Muhtasham of Kashan. Further checking needed. Incomplete. Richly illuminated throughout. The pages written on one side, pasted on cloth-backed card and arranged in concertina form.</note>
                     <incipit>Al-salam ay sayah-at khurshid-i rabb al-'alamin</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For Muhtasham see Rieu, ii, pp. 665-6.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No 1447.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For Edmonstone's bequest see the Donations Register under November 6 1841, p. 408 and J.R.A.S., viii, Annual Report, p. x, Proceedings, p. xxxi.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
